Matthew Fischer (mfischer@isca.uiowa.edu) wrote:
: A while ago I was trying to find out exactly how the DES algorithm works, 
: and I was unable to find a plain-english explanation on the internet, and 
: all the good books had been ripped-off from the library. I tried wading 
: through various C sources (I don't know too much C), but that was too 
: much work. Finally I got my hands on a book (Cryptography And Data 
: Security, DER Denning).

: So now I have typed up a short DES how-to file. It is designed to tell 
: you everything you need to know to use the DES algorithm in plain 
: English. It is meant to be distributed electronically and as freely as 
: export laws will allow, ie only in USA and Canada.

: I am wondering if there is any interest in such a thing, and also if I 
: have recreated something that already exists on the net that I was just 
: unable to find before. If there is interest I will post this to sci.crypt 
: with a distribution of usa,ca.

: (I assume this will be perfectly legal as long as it stays in the USA and 
: Canada. The algorithm is not copyrighted, to my knowledge.)


: Matthew Fischer

: mfischer@kahless.isca.uiowa.edu


